@government
go-to: menu

The German Republic, called by some of our detractors as the "Weimar Republic", is a semi-presidential republic with a parliament, called the "Parliament of Democracy of Reddit". Both the president and the parliament have important governance roles.

The Parliament is elected based on a FPTP system, without electoral districts. The Reichstag then elects the Speaker and the cabinet is appointed by the president, who are responsible for government.

The President is elected by a national direct vote, in up to three rounds. The second round is used if the first round does not result in a majority for one candidate; the top three candidates move to the second round, and if the second round again results in no majority, a third round between the top two candidates is held. If this round results in a tie, the parliament elects the president. The role of the president is to represent the DoR, as well as appointing the cabinet and governing the nation as a whole.

The DoR is divided into a number of states, each of which have their own governments with some responsibilities.

