@parties
go-to: menu

<span style="color: #aa0f24;">**RGA**</span> - <span style="color: #aa0f24;">*Red Grits Alliance*</span> - this is us. We are a socialist and democratic party of the working class. We are the foremost defenders of Reddit socialism. The modern SPD was founded by Yes Tuesday, a liberal socialist, as a broad pan-socialist party.

**<span style="color: #ea2cdd;">**PP**</span>** - <span style="color: #ea2cdd;">*Progressive Party*</span> - a centrist to center-left party supported by many progressives and social democrats. For the September presidential election, we agreed on a <span style="color: #ea2cdd;">**Popular**</span> <span style="color: #aa0f24;">**Front**</span> with them, to defeat the <span style="color: #1345b1;">**Conservative**</span> candidate . [? if year >= 1930 or chancellor = "Brüning" : They have appeared to take a more conservative turn recently, with the rise of Brüning and the party leader, Ludwig Kaas. ?]

Current relations: [+ z_relation : relationships +]

# TODO: replace this with the german state party after 1930
<span style="color: #bf353a;">**Center-Left**</span> - <span style="color: #bf353a;">*various center-lefts*</span> - The various center-left and left-wing parties and independents left of the Progressives, however skeptical of our "radicalism". They have so far failed to merge into a single party.  [? if year >= 1930 : They have recently reformed themselves as the German State Party (DStP). ?]

Current relations: [+ ddp_relation : relationships +]

**PLP** - *Progressive-Liberal Party* - a centrist party, seeking a middle way between the <span style="color: #ea2cdd;">**Progressives**</span> and the <span style="color: #1345b1;">**Conservatives**</span>. They are rather unimportant.

Current relations: [+ dvp_relation : relationships +]

**CP** - *Conservative Party* (German National People's Party) - a right-wing nationalist-conservative party. They have been rather unfriendly towards us and the other parties of the left. The founder of the <span style="color: #4972af;">**DoR**</span>, Hour Employment, has also founded them.

Current relations: [+ dnvp_relation : relationships +]

**Far-Left** - <span style="color: #700000;">*various far-lefts*</span> - socialists and communists left of the RGA. They are rather small and unimportant. Our controversial alliance with the <span style="color: #ea2cdd;">**Progressives**</span> has largely lead to their continued growth. They might aim to form a party in the future.

Current relations: [+ kpd_relation : relationships +]

[? if sapd_formed: SAPD - Sozialistische Arbeiterpartei Deutschlands (Socialist Worker's Party of Germany) - a party recently formed in a split from the SPD, the SAPD is essentially an agglomeration of various left-wing splinter groups between the SPD and KPD. ?]

**Far-Right** - *various far-rights* - they are rather unimportant. However, if they were to rise, they could become the largest enemy of the <span style="color: #4972af;">**DoR**</span>.

Current relations: [+ nsdap_relation : relationships +]

**Other parties** - there is a multitude of small parties across the entire political spectrum. They are practically unimportant.

